SIMPLE: simular
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Simular
<hw>Sim"u*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. L.
<ets>simulator</ets>, F. <ets>simulateur</ets>. See
<er>Simulate</er>.]</ety> <def>One who pretends to be what he is not;
one who, or that which, simulates or counterfeits something; a
pretender.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Christ calleth the Pharisees hypocrites, that is to say,
<qex>simulars</qex>, and painted sepulchers.</q>
<rj><qau>Tyndale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Simular</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Simular
<hw>Sim"u*lar</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>False; specious;
counterfeit.</def> <mark>[R. & Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Thou
<xex>simular</xex> man of virtue.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Simulate</ent>⟦br⟧
